ility for deciding one way or another is reconcilable with the findings of empirical science, but not with the metaphysical doctrine of determinism.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 4aDeterminismus. 4aMetaphysik. 4aWillensfreiheit. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Metaphysics.2bisacsh  aDeterminism.  aFreedom of Will.  aMetaphysics.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2017 Part 1z978311076249508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2017z978311071954308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2017z9783110540550oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Philosophy 2017z9783110548228oZDB-23-DPH0 cEPUBz97831105334840 cprintz978311053345340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783110534511zOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110534511zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110534511/original  a978-3-11-071954-3 DG Plus eBook-Package 2017b2017  a978-3-11-076249-5 DG Plus DeG Package 2017 Part 1b2017  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb2017  aZDB-23-DPHb2017  aZDB-23-GOA